{"questionId":"7407","questionHtml":"<p>Technetium-99m (<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{}_{43}^{99{\\text{m}}}{\\text{Tc}}\">\n  <msubsup>\n    <mrow>\n\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>43</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>99</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>m</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </msubsup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>Tc</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>) has a half-life of 6.0 hours. Calculate the percentage of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{}_{43}^{99{\\text{m}}}{\\text{Tc}}\">\n  <msubsup>\n    <mrow>\n\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>43</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>99</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>m</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </msubsup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>Tc</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;remaining in a sample of the radioisotope after two days.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em><strong>ALTERNATIVE 1:</strong></em></p>\n<p>«<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{40}}{{6.0}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>40</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>6.0</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> =» 8&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{t_{\\frac{1}{2}}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mfrac>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </mfrac>\n      </mrow>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>/8 half-lives «required» ✔</p>\n<p>% remaining&nbsp;= «(0.5)<sup>8</sup> × 100 =» 0.39 «%» ✔</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>ALTERNATIVE 2:</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>λ</em> =&nbsp;«<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{0.693}}{{6.0}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0.693</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>6.0</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> =» 0.1155 ✔</p>\n<p>% remaining&nbsp;= «100 × <em>e</em><sup>–0.1155 × 48</sup>&nbsp;=» 0.39 «%» ✔</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Award <strong>[2]</strong> for correct final answer.</em></p>\n<p><em>Accept “0.32 «%»” in <strong>ALTERNATIVE 2</strong>.</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"7407","referenceCode":"18N.3.hl.TZ0.22b.i","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Technetium-99m ( 43 99 m Tc ) has a half-life of 6.0 hours. Calculate the percentage of 43 99 m Tc remaining in a sample of the radioisotope after two days.","paper":"3","level":"hl","questionNumber":"b.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Options","Options","D: Medicinal chemistry","D.8 Nuclear medicine (HL only)","Options","D: Medicinal chemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}